# AKOS Inter-Wave Regression Discipline

Use this rule whenever closing a wave inside a multi-wave initiative
(I86 precedent: 12+ waves; future analogous coordinators). Codifies
operator decision **D-IH-86-BK** (operator-ratified the wave-close
regression cadence as discipline rather than agent-discretion,
2026-05-21). Mechanical companion to
[`INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION_DISCIPLINE.md).

This rule does **not** define the doctrine — that lives in the canonical.
This rule names the mechanical bar that future agents and operators
inherit by default when closing any wave of a multi-wave initiative.

## When this rule applies

A wave-close is in scope for this rule when **any** of:

- The parent initiative is registered in [`INITIATIVE_REGISTRY.csv`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/Compliance/canonicals/INITIATIVE_REGISTRY.csv) and carries a wave-cadence master-roadmap (cluster coordinator pattern; I86 precedent).
- The wave's deliverables span ≥ 2 canonicals OR ≥ 2 cursor rules OR touch any canonical CSV.
- The wave is named in a cluster-coordinator master-roadmap §"Waves" section.
- The wave's UAT report would fire ≥ 2 UAT classes per `compose_UAT` in [`UAT_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/UAT_DISCIPLINE.md) §4.

Waves NOT in scope: trivial single-commit chore waves (typo fixes; link-rot fixes; formatting normalisations) per the canonical's §4 Exception 3.

## RULE 1 — Run the 13-dimension sweep before the wave's UAT verdict (binding)

Every in-scope wave-close MUST execute the 13-dimension regression sweep before the wave's UAT report verdict line is filled in. The sweep output (`reports/regression-sweep-<date>.md` under the wave's parent initiative folder) is a §3.3 row in the wave's UAT report under the regression class.

The 13 dimensions are defined in [`INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION_DISCIPLINE.md) §2. Summary:

| # | Dimension | Probe heuristic |
|:--|:---|:---|
| 1 | decision_lineage | FK-resolve DECISION_REGISTER decision_id ↔ canonical frontmatter ratifying_decisions; bidirectional |
| 2 | forward_charter_carryover | Glob prior canonicals; resolve forward_charters against subsequent waves' deliverables + OPS_REGISTER |
| 3 | validator_ramp_consistency | Diff verification-profiles.json + release-gate.py across the wave; surface threshold changes without paired decision |
| 4 | canonical_csv_pair_completeness | For each new CSV under canonicals/dimensions/, verify Pydantic + validator + Supabase mirror + PRECEDENCE row |
| 5 | sop_runbook_pairing | FK-resolve process_list.csv item_id → SOP + runbook paths; AC-HUMAN + AC-AUTOMATION both present |
| 6 | uat_report_class_completeness | For closed INITIATIVE_REGISTRY rows, verify UAT classes match `compose_UAT` output |
| 7 | render_trail_audience_match | Re-run `scripts/validate_external_render_trail.py --strict --strict-freshness` |
| 8 | brand_baseline_register_match | Re-run `scripts/validate_brand_baseline_reality_drift.py` |
| 9 | cross_area_breakthrough_announcement | FK-resolve new PEOPLE_DESIGN_PATTERN_REGISTRY pattern_ids → announcement evidence under reports/cross-area-breakthrough-*.md |
| 10 | deploy_evidence_completeness | For each Wave-N-P* file-row with repo != openclaw-akos, verify deploy_id + state=READY + HTTP 200 hero route |
| 11 | cursor_rule_skill_pairing | For each new akos-*.mdc, verify paired skill exists OR forward-charter row exists |
| 12 | operator_scratchpad_continuity | Verify last operator-scratchpad entry timestamp ≥ last wave-close commit timestamp; decisions cited |
| 13 | role_process_pairing_completeness | When scenario has new role_mint OR new process_mint in the closing wave: bidirectional FK check between baseline_organisation.csv role rows and process_list.csv role_owner cells — every new role has ≥1 paired process_list row (ghost-role check; severity low for non-planned/non-gated roles); every new process has its role_owner FK resolvable (orphan-process check; severity high). Codified at Wave P per D-IH-86-CL: operator's "that's a doctrine" framing on paired-mint completeness. INFO at mint; FAIL flip at Wave R close per D-IH-86-CR. |

7 dimensions (1-6, 12) are baseline + always fire. 6 dimensions (7-11, 13) are conditional per the `compose_REGRESSION` rule in `INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION_DISCIPLINE.md` §3.

## RULE 2 — Findings disposition via inline-ratify 5-option enum (binding)

Every WARN or FAIL finding from the sweep MUST be dispositioned via an inline `AskQuestion` gate per [`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc) + the paired [`inline-ratify-craft`](../skills/inline-ratify-craft/SKILL.md) skill, using the 5-option enum codified in `INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION_DISCIPLINE.md` §6:

1. **rework-now** (default for FAIL on baseline dimensions).
2. **forward-charter-next-wave** (default for WARN on conditional dimensions).
3. **defer-OPS** (default for INFO).
4. **accept-as-canon** (operator ratifies the drift was deliberate; appends contra-precedent + decision row).
5. **escalate-to-blocker-tracker** (cannot be dispositioned in-chat; mints `_blockers/<slug>-tracker.md` per [`akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc`](akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc)).

When findings exceed 10, the agent splits the gates into 2 `AskQuestion` batches (per inline-ratify-craft Principle 5 batching guidance). When findings exceed 20, the agent halts and proposes splitting the wave into Wave-M + Wave-M.5 (the bandwidth recovery pattern). Per `akos-inline-ratification.mdc` Time-box section: 24h+ operator silence + clean validators + reversible dispositions auto-default to the recommended option; irreversible dispositions NEVER auto-default.

## RULE 3 — Sweep cadence per canonical §4 (binding)

Default cadence: every wave-close. Exceptions (codified in `INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION_DISCIPLINE.md` §4):

- **Chore-only waves**: MAY skip the 5 conditional dimensions; baseline 7 still fire.
- **Continuous-closure initiatives (5+ daily waves)**: MAY skip 2 of every 3 wave-closes IF operator-explicit decision row records the deferral.
- **Single-commit chore waves**: exempt entirely.

No other exemptions. "We're in a hurry" / "we'll do it next wave" / "operator wants to ship" are NOT exemptions per the operator's 2026-05-21 framing.

## RULE 4 — Self-test step wired into pre_commit (binding from D-IH-86-BO ratification)

The runbook `scripts/inter_wave_regression_sweep.py --self-test` mode verifies the 13 probe functions exist + return well-formed `RegressionFindingRow` Pydantic models. The self-test runs at every `py scripts/verify.py pre_commit` invocation via [`config/verification-profiles.json`](../../config/verification-profiles.json) `validate_inter_wave_regression_self_test` step + [`scripts/release-gate.py`](../../scripts/release-gate.py) `run_inter_wave_regression_self_test`.

The full sweep (--wave-closing `<wave-letter>`) runs at wave-close only — NOT at every pre_commit (which would be too expensive). The self-test is the always-on circuit-breaker; the full sweep is the wave-close gate.

Per `D-IH-86-BN` INFO → FAIL ramp:
- Wave M (mint): self-test PASS at pre_commit; full sweep runs once for Wave L deliverables.
- Wave M+1..M+2: full sweep runs at each wave-close; self-test stays PASS.
- Wave M+3 or later: sweep promoted to release-gate INFO advisory at every wave-close commit; eventually FAIL when findings count ≤ 2 across 3+ consecutive waves.

## When this rule does NOT apply

- **Single-commit chore waves** — typo / link-rot / formatting fixes; no canonical CSVs touched.
- **Standalone (non-cluster-coordinator) initiatives** — when an initiative has no wave-cadence master-roadmap, no inter-wave concept applies; the initiative's closure UAT carries the full burden per `akos-planning-traceability.mdc` §"UAT quality bar".
- **Initiatives explicitly scoped to ≤ 1 wave** — the closure UAT bar already covers structural integrity; no inter-wave dimension applies.

## Self-discipline rules for agents

When closing an in-scope wave:

1. **Run the self-test before drafting the wave commit message.** `py scripts/inter_wave_regression_sweep.py --self-test` must PASS; if FAIL, the runbook itself is broken — fix it before continuing.
2. **Run the full sweep before drafting the wave's UAT verdict.** `py scripts/inter_wave_regression_sweep.py --wave-closing <wave-letter>` emits the per-dimension findings table at the dated report path.
3. **Compute findings count before posting the `AskQuestion` batch.** ≤ 10 fits one batch; 11-20 splits into 2 batches; > 20 triggers the wave-split bandwidth-recovery pattern (halt + propose Wave-N.5).
4. **For every PASS-WITH-FOLLOWUP disposition, record a reproducible follow-up.** Either a tracker file under `_trackers/`, an OPS_REGISTER row with a named owner + ETA, OR a candidate-shaped forward-charter file under `_candidates/`.
5. **For every accept-as-canon disposition, append the contra-precedent.** The affected canonical's frontmatter `last_review_decision_id` must point to the ratifying decision row that records the intentional drift; the canonical's body must add a §"Contra-precedent ratification" sub-section citing the decision.
6. **For every escalate-to-blocker-tracker disposition, mint the tracker file.** The tracker MUST follow the shape in `akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc` §"Blocker-tracker file shape (binding template)".
7. **Update operator-scratchpad before the wave's commit.** The wave's summary, decision IDs, gaps, and forward-pointers MUST land in `docs/wip/intelligence/operator-scratchpad.md` before the wave's atomic commit lands (dimension 12 is then guaranteed to PASS).

